==Indonesian==

===Etymology===
Common Oceanian, compare Hawaiian ''[[ala]]''

===Noun===
'''jalan'''

# [[path]], [[road]], [[street]]
#* '''''jalan''' [[raya]]''
#*: highway, [[main]] '''road'''
#* '''''jalan''' [[satu arah]]''
#*: [[one-way]] '''street'''
#* ''[[peta]] '''jalan'''''
#*: '''street''' [[map]]
#* ''[[lampu]] '''jalan'''''
#*: '''street''' [[lamp]]
# [[route]], [[way]], [[course]]
# [[way]], [[manner]]

===Verb===
'''jalan'''  {{intransitive}}

# to go on/foward
# to [[walk]]
# to [[pass]]
#* The verb '''jalan''' is an informal variant of [[berjalan]].

===Derived terms===
* [[jalanan]]: path
* [[perjalanan]]
* [[sejalan]]: [[parallel]], to be in [[accordance]] with
* [[berjalan]]: to [[walk]]
* [[berjalan-jalan]]: to take a walk
* [[jalan-jalan]]: to go for a [[stroll]]
* [[menjalani]]: to walk on; to [[undergo]], to [[endure]]; to go through a period of your life
* [[menjalankan]]: to drive, to operate; to start, to put into operation; to carry out, to perform

